can you tell me anything about colon cancer thank you please tell me anything you now colon cancer is malignant tissue that grows in the wall of the colon the majority of tumors begin when normal tissue in the colon wall forms an adenomatous polyp or pre cancerous growth projecting from the colon wall as this polyp grows larger the tumor is formed this process can take many years which allows time for early detection with screening tests unfortunately the early stages of colon cancer may not have any symptoms this is why it is important to have screening tests done even though you may feel well as the polyp grows into a tumor it may bleed or obstruct the colon causing symptoms these symptoms include bleeding from the rectum blood in the stool or toilet after a bowel movement a change in the shape of the stool i e thinning cramping pain in the abdomen feeling the need to have a bowel movement when you don't actually have to as you can see these symptoms can also be caused by conditions other than cancer if you experience these symptoms you should be checked by a doctor Prostate cancer Stomach cancer Endometrial cancer Familial adenomatous polyposis Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Hemorrhoid Lung cancer Ovarian cancer Mesothelioma Crohn's disease Endometriosis Fecal incontinence Diverticulosis Breast cancer Constipation Urinary incontinence Cervical cancer Coeliac disease Diarrhea Radiation therapy Brain tumor Obstetrics Ulcerative colitis Malignant melanoma Sigmoidoscopy Irritable bowel syndrome Metastasis Colonoscopy Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Hypoglycemia Hirschsprung's disease Gastrointestinal stromal tumor Esophageal cancer Testicular cancer Androgen insensitivity syndrome Fecal occult blood Folic acid Aspartame Traumatic brain injury Medicine Multiple myeloma Tumor Carcinogenesis Renal cell carcinoma Kaposi's sarcoma Leukemia Barium enema Hepatocellular carcinoma Cancer of the larynx Oncology Atherosclerosis Kidney Rheumatoid arthritis Malaria Miscarriage Syring